results.name: Number of nodes in rooted tree with GF2X-Matula number n.
link: A. Karttunen, Scheme-program for computing this sequence.
Index entries for sequences operating on GF(2)[X]-polynomials
example: GF2X-Matula numbers for unoriented rooted trees are constructed otherwise just like the standard Matula-Goebel numbers (cf. A061773), but instead of normal factorization in N, one factorizes in polynomial ring GF(2)[X] as follows. Here IR(n) is the n-th irreducible polynomial (A014580(n)) and X stands for GF(2)[X]-multiplication (A048720):
Counting the vertices (marked with x's and o's) of each tree above, we get the eight initial terms of this sequence: 1,2,3,3,5,4,4,4,6.
